alti is basically a Digital Elevation Model (DTM) to Bitmap file (BMP) converter built in standard C.

alti reads from ASCII XYZ files. It stores its informations into memory, allowing data to be process. It then exports results into Bitmap file format. The processing of the data presently include elevation range recognition. 


To run the program

use these parameters :
alti path/to/xyz path/to/bmp low up

Exemple:
alti data/sample.xyz file 400 400


